@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<style>
    .terms-section {
        background: #f8f9fa;
        padding: 60px 0;
    }

    .terms-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

        .terms-header h2 {
            font-size: 32px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #333;
        }

    .terms-content {
        background: white;
        padding: 30px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

        .terms-content h4 {
            margin-top: 20px;
            color: #007bff;
        }

        .terms-content p {
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #555;
        }
</style>

<!-- Terms and Conditions Section -->
<div class="container terms-section">
    <div class="terms-header">
        <h2>Terms and Conditions for Equipment Management & Lab Experiments</h2>
        <p class="text-muted"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> [Insert Date]</p>
    </div>
    <div class="terms-content">
        <p>Welcome to the [Your Lab Name] Equipment Management and Lab Experiment Portal. By using our services, you agree to comply with the following terms and conditions. Please read them carefully.</p>

        <h4>1. General Guidelines</h4>
        <p>1.1 These terms govern the booking of lab slots and the usage of equipment in our facility.</p>
        <p>1.2 All users must adhere to the lab safety protocols and operational guidelines.</p>
        <p>1.3 Any misuse of equipment or violation of lab rules may result in access restrictions.</p>

        <h4>2. Slot Booking</h4>
        <p>2.1 Users must book a time slot in advance through the official booking system.</p>
        <p>2.2 Bookings are on a first-come, first-served basis and subject to availability.</p>
        <p>2.3 Cancellations must be made at least [X] hours in advance to allow other users to book the slot.</p>
        <p>2.4 Repeated no-shows may result in restricted access to future bookings.</p>

        <h4>3. Equipment Usage</h4>
        <p>3.1 Users are responsible for handling all equipment with care and following the provided instructions.</p>
        <p>3.2 Any malfunction or damage must be reported immediately to the lab supervisor.</p>
        <p>3.3 Equipment should be returned to its designated place after use.</p>
        <p>3.4 Unauthorized removal of equipment from the lab is strictly prohibited.</p>

        <h4>4. Lab Conduct & Safety</h4>
        <p>4.1 Users must wear appropriate safety gear while conducting experiments.</p>
        <p>4.2 Eating, drinking, and inappropriate behavior inside the lab are strictly prohibited.</p>
        <p>4.3 Users must follow all instructions given by lab supervisors and staff.</p>
        <p>4.4 Any accidents or injuries must be reported immediately.</p>

        <h4>5. Liability & Responsibility</h4>
        <p>5.1 The lab is not responsible for any personal injury resulting from improper equipment use.</p>
        <p>5.2 Users are liable for any damage caused due to negligence or mishandling.</p>
        <p>5.3 The institution reserves the right to modify, suspend, or terminate access to lab facilities at its discretion.</p>

        <h4>6. Amendments & Updates</h4>
        <p>6.1 These terms and conditions may be updated periodically. Users will be notified of any changes.</p>
        <p>6.2 Continued use of the lab facilities constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.</p>

        <p><strong>By booking a slot or using the lab equipment, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agreed to these terms and conditions.</strong></p>

        <p>For any inquiries, please contact <strong>[Your Lab Contact Information]</strong>.</p>
    </div>
</div>
